2.Material_Comm: The scribe indented the first line, thus creating a _vacat_ to begin. From a literary point of view, this cannot prove that any material preceded the text here, but rather if any text did precede it would have to make a literary unit.
2.Label: T-S_10K6_1r.tif:0002

1060.Material_Comm: There is a small lacuna in the parchment that overlaps with {{sign: 14}}. The flaking of the ink and perhaps the lacuna is perhaps related to the manuscript having been creased here. See {{sign: 1054}}.

55.Palaeo_Comm: Whereas the outline of the character remains visible, some of the ink has flaked off the surface. There could have been a crease in the parchment, since the flaking off ink is also apparent on {{sign: 13}}, {{sign: 14}}, {{sign:56}}, {{sign: 94}}, {{sign: 95}}, and {{sign: 96}}. Thus, it could have been a crease or some defect on the parchment. cf. {{sign: 1054}}.
55.Label: T-S_10K6_1r.tif:0055
